### Hadith 1:601

*Narrated Malik bin Huwairth:*

I came to the Prophet with some men from my tribe and stayed with him
for twenty nights. He was kind and merciful to us. When he realized our
longing for our families, he said to us, "Go back and stay with your
families and teach them the religion, and offer the prayer and one of
you should pronounce the Adhan for the prayer when its time is due and
the oldest one amongst you should lead the prayer."

